text.section:
Each complaint shall:
Be in writing;
Identify specifically the person or organization against whom the complaint is made;
Set forth the facts relating to the violation alleged and any other supporting information which may have a bearing on the matter;
Contain the name, address, telephone number, facsimile number, and e-mail address, if available, of the complainant; and
Be signed by the complainant as the truth of the statements contained in the complaint by the complainant.

The notification shall name the person or organization complained against, the complainant, the violations alleged, and the facts presented in the complaint and shall notify the person or organization complained against and the employer of:
The fact that the complaint shall be answered, the steps for answering the complaint, and the action to be taken if the complaint is not answered;
The timeframe and steps in the proceedings of a complaint;
The rights of the parties, including the right to counsel; and
The right to testify at any hearing.
